He had been his lifelong true and ⁴steadfast friend, and was one of the first to predict Bishop Monahan's elevation to the Episcopate. It was also his wish that he would be his* successor. Moreover, Dr. Smith, although born in the Diocese of Meath, on the confines of Ardagh, at Ballymachugh, always considered himself more an Ardagh than :a Meath man.
